<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06278009 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06278009 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  PROFESSIONAL; HOCKEY; SAFETY; PRODUCT; PROFILE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  GREG Harrison, the man who makes masks for 70 professional hockey goalies,can't stand white.;   &quot;It's just too plain,&quot; he says. &quot;It's like sending out acanvas without anything on it. White's like generic. White's like nothing.&quot;  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Living  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  THE MAN BEHIND THE MASKS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  See related articles pages 1L and 8L  </MEMO><TEXT>     So for 21 years, Harrison has been making masks that look like something --a roaring lion, Indian headdress, fly-fishing hook -- whether players want himto or not.;   When Pete Peeters was with Philadelphia, he once insisted onplain white. &quot;I couldn't do it,&quot; Harrison says. He painted it black.;   FrankPietrangelo, a goalie for the Pittsburgh Penguins, left the design of his maskup to Harrison, who created a striking pattern of yellow triangles on a blackbackground. &quot;It's the bomb shelter symbol,&quot; Harrison says. &quot;They weren't doingso well at the time. They were getting bombed.&quot;  </TEXT><BYLINE>  -- Michalene Busico  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911004  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  8L  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  142  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday, October 4, 199100278009,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>